[3] China - 9 cases
Date: 20 Sep 2011
Source: Reuters [edited]
http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/09/20/us-polio-china-idUSTRE78J48320110920


WHO reports polio outbreak in China, warns of spread
----------------------------------------------------
Polio has broken out in China for the 1st time since 1999 after being
imported from Pakistan, and there is a high risk of the crippling
virus spreading further during the annual Haj pilgrimage, the World
Health Organization said on Tuesday [20 Sep 2011].

A total of 9 cases have been confirmed in China, and polio is now
considered to have spread nationwide in Pakistan, mainly due to
insecurity that has halted vaccination campaigns in areas including
the Khyber tribal region, a WHO spokesman said.

"The WHO rates as 'high' the risk of further international spread of
wild polio virus from Pakistan, particularly given the expected
large-scale population movements associated with Umra and the upcoming
Haj...in the coming months," the Geneva-based body said in a
statement.

Haj is the main annual Muslim pilgrimage to Mecca in Saudi Arabia,
which is due to start in November. Umra refers to other pilgrimages to
Mecca, which can take place any time of the year.

--
